{
  "text": "where the threshold H min is an adjustable constant that depends on pressure. The main difference in CAM3, compared to CCM3 and CAM2, is that H min does not have a stability dependence and H min \u0545 0.91 for all existing model configurations. In the previous models, the stability dependence resulted in H min \u03fe 0.99 over most of the tropical upper troposphere. Clouds then turned on or off abruptly due to minor variations in relative humidity. As in CAM2 and CCM3, a marine stratus parameterization based on [CITATION_1] gives a lower bound on f s for cells that are at least one-half ocean covered. This parameterization is only active over limited regions off the west coasts of continents.",
